Protocol.Name: Skyline Example Matrix
Protocol.Description: Example that is using the Matrix Helper Class with matrix and table parameters

Information.Subtext: This single parameter contains all crosspoint values. This can be used with an external virtual driver that combines different elements into on big router control.
This parameter controls if the Matrix View is displayed or not.
This parameter controls if the Table View is displayed or not.
Matrix representation of the router control.
This single parameter contains all matrix information in JSON format. This can be used with an external virtual driver that combines different elements into one big router control.
This parameter indicates whether the matrix parameter and or router control tables are being used.
Table representation of the router control. This table will contain the information of the inputs.
Contains the one based input number.
Contains the label of the input.
Indicates whether the input is enabled or not.
Indicates whether the input is locked or not.
Custom notes can be added for a particular input.
Table representation of the router control. This table will contain the information of the outputs.
Contains the one based output number.
Contains the label of the output.
Indicates whether the output is enabled or not.
Indicates whether the output is locked or not.
Custom notes can be added for a particular output.
Contains which input is connected to this output. Note: tables only support one input per output.
